### Bug 2: Flexible Sprint Goal Met Calculation

**Problem:** Sprint goal was checked with exact `===` match. Tasks that progressed **beyond** their goal (e.g., goal = "Testing", status = "Completed") were not shown as met.

**Fix:** Created [hasMetSprintGoal()](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/utils.ts) that uses `WORKFLOW_STATUSES` index ordering — `currentIndex >= goalIndex` means met.

Applied in 5 files:
- [utils.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/utils.ts) — new helper function
- [api.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/api.ts) — timeline segment `isCompleted`
- [TaskOverview.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/TaskOverview.tsx) — sorting, stats, display
- [DailyMeetingView.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx) — [DraggableTaskCard](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#511-700) + [SquadsView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#2004-2597)
